William Woodruff
Professor John Beckett writes:
In his sequel to William Woodruff (September 25) he states that "in 1946 he resumed studies in economic history at Oxford and in 1950 he won a Houblon-Norman research scholarship... at the same time he was studying for a bachelor's degree, a master's degree and a doctorate."
