The international exhibition of the Frankfurt book awaits for this edition more than 7 thousand exhibitors from 102 different countries who will occupy the 171.790 square meters of the exhibition with more than 403,000 titles on display and with Turkey as an honored guest.
It will be the undersecretary of the Ministry of cultural goods and activities Francisco Maria Giro to represent the Italian government at the opening ceremony of the Italian pavilion: Italy will be institutionally and effectively present with a point Italy - 264 square meters of exhibition space.
An encounter with the print will follow in the Room Struktur in Hall 5.0 of the Buchmesse: this will be the occasion to present numbers, trends and prospects on the state of publishing houses in Italy.
According to the data, the weight of books by foreign authors progressively decreases over the total of Italian production, and in particular that for adults and adolescents.
Steve Fossett's plane found, millionaire missing a year ago
The remains of the plane of Steve Fossett, the millionaire who disappeared on September 3, 2007 while flying over the Nevada desert, have been found.
The debris has been found on a plateau at an altitude of 3,000 meters, in the area of the Sierra Nevada of Mammoth Lakes, on the border between California and Nevada.
Inside the plane, there were no human remains.
Wood County Sheriff John Anderson said: “The plane has been located, we have sent a squad, and now we have confirmation that it is what Steve Fossett was flying on the day of his disappearance.”
He said no human remains had been found on or around the plane.
The 63-year-old billionaire was presumed dead in February.
The American office for the safety of the transports (Ntsb) has announced that some hours after the sighting of the remains, a squadron of investigators has been sent that has identified the apparatus: it is own of the Bellanca 8kcab, dispersed since September 3, 2007, when Fossett took off from Yerington in Nevada for a flight of three hours.
Yesterday, still in California, not far from the border of Nevada, some personal remains of Fossett have been found by a couple near his home in Mammoth Lakes.
These are two documents with the name of Fossett, both issued by the Federal Aviation Administration of Illinois, cash and a sweatshirt.
The search for Fossett had been interrupted a month after his disappearance.
The millionaire had conquered a place in history thanks to a long series of firsts.
In 2002, at the sixth attempt, he had become the first man to complete the world tour in a hot air balloon: two lonely weeks of flight.
Three years later he had made the world tour by plane and without stopovers.
Among his records, also that for having flown at 15,445 meters above sea level, over the Andes, but with a co-pilot.
Glk, the advertising you don’t expect
An out-of-the-box SUV with an original and well-established design with defined lines and determined angles.
This is, in short, Glk the latest born among the "compact" all-terrain trucks of the house of the star with which Mercedes-Benz has sought to give a window of novelty in this sector.
Proper for the content outside the traditional, it will be unexpected and unconventional, the communication that accompanied the launch of the suv Glk, available in the showrooms Mercedes-Benz from next October 17.
The advertising campaign that accompanied the debut of the new car will launch an unprecedented mode of communication through a 3D advertising campaign, used for the first time in Italy by a car brand.
A project with maxi-posters, articulated in three different phases, that will dominate the central shopping street of Milan, avenue Como, until November 15th.
The first phase of this new type of communication will begin with the presentation of the car in stereoscopic version and thanks to special glasses distributed on Avenida Como it will be possible to see the new SUV in almost real dimensions and in three-dimensional format.
Indeed, looking at the images you will have the impression that the car comes out of the poster.
Subsequently, through the use of the innovative Elumina8 technology, the new Glk will be illuminated at different times in all its details, to be recomposed into a single image.
Without a doubt Mercedes with this advertising is trying to introduce something new in the stereotype of automotive communication.
Will this formula be able to capture the interest of future buyers? we will see.
